Figure 1:Data Generation Pipeline.
The task proposer agent generates an initial task and the first action based on the website homepage.
The task is then iteratively refined in subsequent steps by the refiner agent.
Finally, the task summarizer agent constructs an overall task description from the action sequence, followed by task verification to assess correctness.

Figure 3:Data composition for Explorer.
Its extensive diversity showcases its potential to train end-to-end generalist web agents.

Figure 4:Experiments with data scaling using Explorer-4B on Mind2Web-Live. We experiment with using 100%, 50%, and 25% of the trajectory data. All results are averaged over three runs. All metrics exhibit improvement with increase in data scale.
Figure 5:Statistics for different error cases in Mind2Web-Live evaluation. Task deviation is the most prevalent error type.
